      "message": "But this doesn’t really belong here. It’s a property of minidumps, not snapshots.\n\nScott and I came up against it in the past. I think we punted because it was a header-only dependency, not a “real” cycle, so we let it stand. But I think that the plan of record, if we ever needed it, was to introduce a new library in minidump for format-related things, like //minidump:minidump_format. That’s where minidump_extensions and minidump_context could live. That way, both minidump and snapshot would be able to depend on minidump_extensions without having to depend on one another.\n\nI think that’s cleaner and more logical. What do you think?",
